# Build outputs
.next/
out/
dist/
.turbo/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Generated by Next on every dev/build, and it CHURNS: its import flips between
# `./.next/dev/types/routes.d.ts` and `./.next/types/routes.d.ts` depending on
# which command ran last, so it produced a spurious diff on almost every branch.
#
# Ignored rather than tolerated, on three pieces of evidence:
#  - the file's own header says it must not be edited — it is an artifact, and its
#    only content points INTO `.next/`, which is already ignored. A committed copy
#    is therefore correct only for whoever ran the matching command last.
#  - Next regenerates it unprompted. Verified 2026-07-19: deleted, then `pnpm build`
#    recreated it (with the build-flavoured import).
#  - it is not needed to typecheck. CI runs `typecheck` BEFORE `build` and the task
#    has no `dependsOn`, so the worry was a fresh checkout failing. Verified in
#    exactly that state — no `.next/`, no `next-env.d.ts` — `tsc --noEmit` exits 0.
#
# The alternative, keeping it and accepting the noise, trains reviewers to skip a
# tracked file. That is the habit that lets a real change through unread.
next-env.d.ts

